ws |title=Bicol region records first cases of COVID-19 |url=https://www.cnnphilippines.com/regional/2020/3/27/bicol-coronavirus.html |accessdate=March 30, 2020 |work=CNN Philippines |date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Camarines Sur]]<ref name=\"Inquirer-CovidBicol\">{{cite news |last1=Arguelles |first1=Mar S. |title=Bicol records 4th COVID-19 positive case |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1250150/bicol-records-4th-covid-19-positive-case |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Philippine Daily Inquirer |date=March 28, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n**''[[Naga City, Camarines Sur|Naga]]''<ref name=bicolfirst/>\n*[[Western Visayas]] (Region VI)\n**[[Antique]]<ref name=\"antique\">{{cite news |title=Antique confirms first case of COVID-19 infection |url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/news/regions/732995/antique-confirms-first-case-of-covid-19-infection/story/ |accessdate=April 7, 2020 |work=GMA News |date=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Aklan]]<ref name=\"PNAGovPH-CovidWestVisayas\">{{cite news |last1=Momblan |first1=Gail |title=W. Visayas confirms 9 new Covid-19 cases |url=https://www.pna.gov.ph/articles/1098069 |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Philippine News Agency |date=March 27, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n**''[[Bacolod]]''<ref name=\"PIAGovPH-CovidBacolod\">{{cite news |last1=Lambatin |first1=Lorenzo O. |title=Bacolod PUI is 1st COVID-19 positive case in WV |url=https://pia.gov.ph/news/articles/1036790 |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Philippine Information Agency |date=March 21, 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"PNAGovPH-CovidWestVisayas\" />\n**[[Capiz]]<ref name=\"PNAGovPH-CovidWestVisayas\" />\n**[[Iloilo]]<ref name=\"PNAGovPH-CovidWestVisayas\" />\n**''[[Iloilo City]]''<ref name=\"PNAGovPH-CovidWestVisayas\" />\n**[[Negros Occidental]]<ref name=\"MB-CovidNegrosOcc\">{{cite news |last1=Masculino |first1=Glazyl |title=Negros Occ brgy declared 'hot zone' after 1st COVID-19 positive case |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2020/03/29/negros-occ-brgy-declared-hot-zone-after-1st-covid-